article.headline: Tulane 77, New Orleans 66
article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Chris Moore, Vincent Camper and David Gomez each scored 16 points Tuesday to lead Tulane to a 77-66 victory over New Orleans. Gomez also had 10 rebounds while Camper had nine assists. What should have been a cross-town matchup was played at College Station because both Louisiana teams were forced from their homes by Hurricane Katrina. The Privateeers (1-1) used a 14-4 run at the start of the second half to take a 49-39 lead with 13:47 left to play. Tulane (1-0) then went on a 15-2 run to take a 54-51 lead with 8:03 left. Gomez got half of his 16 points during that run. Tulane took the lead for good on a 3-pointer by Moore that made it 65-63. New Orleans made it a one-point game on a free throw by Wayne Williams with 3:09 left, but Tulane then went on a 12-2 run. Bo McCalebb led New Orleans with 23 points and James Parlow added 18. Jamie McNeilly had 13.
